# TypeScript/React Rules

## Types & Interfaces
- Use `interface` for object shapes that may be extended
- Use `type` for unions, intersections, tuples, mapped types
- Prefer string literal unions over `enum`
- Add explicit types to all exported functions, shared utilities, public class methods
- Let TypeScript infer obvious local variable types
- Extract repeated inline object shapes into named types/interfaces

## React 19 Specifics
- React Compiler is enabled — no need for `useMemo`/`useCallback` in most cases
- Define component props with named `interface` or `type`
- Type callback props explicitly
- Do NOT use `React.FC`
- Use Server Components where applicable (Next.js context)

## Immutability
- Use spread operator for immutable updates
- Use `Readonly<T>` for props that shouldn't mutate
- Never mutate state directly — always use setter functions

## Error Handling
```typescript
function getErrorMessage(error: unknown): string {
  if (error instanceof Error) return error.message
  return 'Unexpected error'
}

async function loadUser(userId: string): Promise<User> {
  try {
    return await riskyOperation(userId)
  } catch (error: unknown) {
    logger.error('Operation failed', error)
    throw new Error(getErrorMessage(error))
  }
}
```

## Input Validation
- Use Zod for schema-based validation
- Infer types from schemas:
```typescript
const userSchema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email(),
  age: z.number().int().min(0).max(150)
})
type UserInput = z.infer<typeof userSchema>
```

## File Organization (Feature-Based)
```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── hero/
│   │   ├── Hero.tsx
│   │   ├── HeroVisual.tsx
│   │   └── hero.css
│   └── ui/
│       ├── Button.tsx
│       └── SurfaceCard.tsx
├── hooks/
│   ├── useDebounce.ts
│   └── useApi.ts
├── lib/
│   ├── api.ts
│   └── utils.ts
├── types/
│   └── index.ts
└── styles/
    ├── tokens.css
    └── global.css
```

## CSS Rules
- Use CSS Custom Properties for design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
- Animate only compositor-friendly properties: `transform`, `opacity`, `clip-path`
- Avoid animating: `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `margin`, `padding`
- Use semantic HTML first — no wrapper `div` stacks when semantic elements exist

## API Calls
- Use the correct API URL by environment (local vs public)
- Always use `credentials: 'include'` for CORS with auth
- Handle errors consistently with the `ApiResponse<T>` pattern

## Performance
- Dynamic import heavy libraries: `const gsap = await import('gsap')`
- Images: explicit `width`/`height`, `loading="lazy"` for below-fold
- Max 2 font families, use `font-display: swap`
- Keep bundle budgets: Landing <150kb JS gzipped, App <300kb
